file: crates/ctx-summarize/src/error.rs
behavior: Defines the unified error enum returned by the summarization runner's fallible operations, covering path validation, prompt/cache access, agent subprocess failures, and access-control/scope gating.
edit_notes:
  - Variants map to specific runner-side checks (path escape guard, deny-by-default access set, scope-approval gate); adding a new failure mode elsewhere in ctx-summarize likely means adding a variant here rather than reusing an existing one.
  - All fields are Strings (paths/details pre-formatted by callers), not PathBuf or source errors, so no error chaining via #[from]/source() is available.
functions:
invariants:
  - AccessDenied and ScopeTooLarge are the only variants carrying structured fields (path+reason, count+max respectively); all others carry a single String.
external_deps:
  - thiserror: derives Display/Error impls from the #[error("...")] format strings.